% You are an expert Python engineer. Implement pdd/story_detection_result.py.

<pdd-dependency>user_story_tests_python.prompt</pdd-dependency>

% Purpose
Provide the stable automation boundary for scoped `pdd detect --stories` runs while
the legacy evaluator continues to return its compatibility tuple.

% Contract
- Serialize schema version `pdd.detect.stories.v1` with a unique invocation ID,
  normalized scope, aggregate outcome, explicit per-story rows, usage/provenance,
  timestamps, and a stable stop reason.
- Every scoped story MUST appear exactly once. Missing, duplicate, conflicting, or
  non-boolean detector rows MUST produce UNKNOWN and MUST NOT contribute to
  `all_pass=true`.
- PASS requires a resolved contract, resolved in-scope prompt links, no errors, and
  an explicit passing detector row. FAIL means evaluation completed and proposed
  changes may be acted on. UNKNOWN means no trustworthy semantic verdict exists.
- Diagnostics use stable codes and redacted messages. JSON MUST NOT contain Rich
  markup, progress output, credentials, local secret paths, or raw provider errors.
- Cost is serialized as a decimal string and distinguishes measured values from
  unavailable values.
- Explicit JSON files are written using fsync plus atomic replacement; interrupted
  writes MUST NOT replace a previous complete result.

% Capabilities
- Adapt legacy story-result dictionaries without changing legacy library callers.
- Produce deterministic compact JSON for stdout.
- Produce schema-valid configuration/infrastructure failure documents.

% Non-responsibilities
- MUST NOT run LLMs, mutate prompts/stories/contracts, discover broader repository
  scope, authenticate, commit, push, reserve credits, or implement hosted retries.
